==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[curriculum]], "course", derived from currere, "to race", + ''vitae'' genitive of ''[[vita#Latin|vita]]'', "life".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kəˈrikjuləm ˈviːtai/}}

===Noun===
'''curriculum vitae''' (''plural'' '''[[curricula vitae]]'''; ''abbreviation:'' '''[[CV]]''')

#A written account of one's life comprising one's [[education]], [[accomplishment]]s, [[work]] [[experience]], [[publication]]s, etc.; especially, one used to apply for a [[job]]

